README.md
     3â†’# Swarm (experimental, educational)
     5â†’> [!IMPORTANT]
     6â†’> Swarm is now replaced by the [OpenAI Agents SDK](https://github.com/openai/openai-agents-python), which is a production-ready evolution of Swarm. The Agents SDK features key improvements and will be actively maintained by the OpenAI team.
     7â†’>
     8â†’> We recommend migrating to the Agents SDK for all production use cases.
     9â†’
    10â†’## Install
    24â†’## Usage
    60â†’## Table of Contents
    72â†’# Overview
    74â†’Swarm focuses on making agent **coordination** and **execution** lightweight, highly controllable, and easily testable.
    75â†’
    76â†’It accomplishes this through two primitive abstractions: `Agent`s and **handoffs**. An `Agent` encompasses `instructions` and `tools`, and can at any point choose to hand off a conversation to another `Agent`.
    77â†’
    78â†’These primitives are powerful enough to express rich dynamics between tools and networks of agents, allowing you to build scalable, real-world solutions while avoiding a steep learning curve.
    79â†’
    80â†’> [!NOTE]
    81â†’> Swarm Agents are not related to Assistants in the Assistants API. They are named similarly for convenience, but are otherwise completely unrelated. Swarm is entirely powered by the Chat Completions API and is hence stateless between calls.
    82â†’
    83â†’## Why Swarm
    89â†’# Examples
    91â†’Check out `/examples` for inspiration! Learn more about each one in its README.
    92â†’
    93â†’- [`basic`](examples/basic): Simple examples of fundamentals like setup, function calling, handoffs, and context variables
    94â†’- [`triage_agent`](examples/triage_agent): Simple example of setting up a basic triage step to hand off to the right agent
    95â†’- [`weather_agent`](examples/weather_agent): Simple example of function calling
    96â†’- [`airline`](examples/airline): A multi-agent setup for handling different customer service requests in an airline context.
    97â†’- [`support_bot`](examples/support_bot): A customer service bot which includes a user interface agent and a help center agent with several tools
    98â†’- [`personal_shopper`](examples/personal_shopper): A personal shopping agent that can help with making sales and refunding orders
    99â†’
   100â†’# Documentation
   104â†’## Running Swarm
   114â†’### `client.run()`
   126â†’#### Arguments
   141â†’#### `Response` Fields
   149â†’## Agents
