examples/triage_agent/README.md
     1â†’# Triage agent
     3â†’This example is a Swarm containing a triage agent, which takes in user inputs and chooses whether to respond directly, or triage the request
     4â†’to a sales or refunds agent.
     5â†’
     6â†’## Setup
     8â†’To run the triage agent Swarm:
     9â†’
    10â†’1. Run
    11â†’
    12â†’```shell
    13â†’python3 run.py
    14â†’```
    15â†’
    16â†’## Evals
    18â†’> [!NOTE]
    19â†’> These evals are intended to be examples to demonstrate functionality, but will have to be updated and catered to your particular use case.
    20â†’
    21â†’This example uses `Pytest` to run eval unit tests. We have two tests in the `evals.py` file, one which
    22â†’tests if we call the correct triage function when expected, and one which assesses if a conversation
    23â†’is 'successful', as defined in our prompt in `evals.py`.
    24â†’
    25â†’To run the evals, run
    26â†’
    27â†’```shell
    28â†’pytest evals.py
    29â†’```

