examples/weather_agent/README.md
     1â†’# Weather agent
     3â†’This example is a weather agent demonstrating function calling with a single agent. The agent has tools to get the weather of a particular city, and send an email.
     4â†’
     5â†’## Setup
     7â†’To run the weather agent Swarm:
     8â†’
     9â†’1. Run
    10â†’
    11â†’```shell
    12â†’python3 run.py
    13â†’```
    14â†’
    15â†’## Evals
    17â†’> [!NOTE]
    18â†’> These evals are intended to be examples to demonstrate functionality, but will have to be updated and catered to your particular use case.
    19â†’
    20â†’This example uses `Pytest` to run eval unit tests. We have two tests in the `evals.py` file, one which
    21â†’tests if we call the `get_weather` function when expected, and one which assesses if we properly do NOT call the
    22â†’`get_weather` function when we shouldn't have a tool call.
    23â†’
    24â†’To run the evals, run
    25â†’
    26â†’```shell
    27â†’pytest evals.py
    28â†’```

